      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> tofu pieces</strong> to a large bowl with<strong> half </strong>your <strong>soy sauce </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Once fully coated, add most of your <strong>cornflour</strong> to the bowl (you’ll use the rest later!) and mix it all together until fully coated</p><p>Once very hot, add the <strong>coated</strong> <strong>tofu</strong> to the pan, and cook for 8-9 min, turning occasionally until golden and crisp (reserve the bowl) – this is your <strong>crispy tofu</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1682435354335-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1682435354335-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1682435354335-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1682435354335-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1682435354335-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the tofu is cooking, wipe out the reserved bowl and add your <strong>medium egg noodles</strong></p><p>Cover the noodles with <strong>boiled water </strong>and stir for 10 secs to separate the noodles</p><p>Set aside to soak for 5-6 min</p><p>Drain the soaked noodles, reserving a cup of <strong>starchy noodle water</strong>, and set aside</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1682435362191-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1682435362191-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1682435362191-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1682435362191-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1682435362191-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim, then slice your<strong> spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Combine your<strong> Chinese rice wine</strong> with your <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong>,<strong> sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> remaining soy sauce</strong>,<strong> white wine vinegar</strong>,<strong>hoisin sauce </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)<strong> </strong>and<strong> remaining cornflour</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up, then add 75ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [110ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and stir it all together – this is your <strong>Chinese-style sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1682435371306-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1682435371306-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1682435371306-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1682435371306-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1682435371306-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>carrot & cabbage slaw mix</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>spring onion</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) to the pan</p><p>Cook for 1-2 min or until slightly softened</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1682435394269-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1682435394269-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1682435394269-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1682435394269-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1682435394269-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once slightly softened, add the <strong>drained noodles </strong>to the pan with the <strong>Chinese-style</strong> <strong>sauce</strong></p><p>Stir it all together and cook for a further 30 secs or until the noodles are coated in the sauce – these are your <strong>Chinese-style hoisin noodles</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy noodle water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1682435408885-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1682435408885-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1682435408885-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1682435408885-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1682435408885-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Chinese-style hoisin noodles</strong> topped with the <strong>crispy tofu</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining chopped spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
